# UI Refinement Phase

Playback reliability is a **protected system**. UI improvements are encouraged.

Read `docs/playback-architecture.md` before any playback-adjacent UI work.

## Protected files (do not modify)

Unless a **reproducible playback bug** is filed and confirmed:

- `src/lib/music/global-player-engine.ts`
- `src/lib/music/spotify-embed-api.ts`
- `src/lib/music/player.ts`
- `src/lib/music/playback-actions.ts`
- `src/stores/playback-store.ts`
- `src/components/music/PlaybackRoot.tsx`
- `src/lib/music/providers/**`

See `.cursor/rules/playback-reliability-protocol.mdc` (Part 1).

## UI may freely change

- Layouts, cards, modals, typography, spacing
- Navigation, responsive behavior, animations
- Global player appearance and positioning
- Card interactions, hover states, visual hierarchy

## Mandatory UI ↔ playback contract

### READ (selectors only)

```ts
usePlaybackStore((s) => s.currentTrack)
usePlaybackStore((s) => s.isPlaying)
// etc.
```

Or `useCardPlayback()` for active/playing + click handler.

### DISPATCH (actions only)

```ts
import {
  playItem,
  togglePlayback,
  seekTo,
  handlePlaybackSurfaceClick,
  expandPlaybackSurface,
  openPlayerSurface,
  closePlayerSurface,
  stopPlayback,
} from "@/lib/music/playback-actions";
```

### Forbidden in UI

- Import engine or provider modules
- `document.createElement('audio'|'iframe')` for playback
- Local `useState` for `isPlaying`, `currentTime`, `duration`, active track
- Duplicate play/pause/open click policy — use `handlePlaybackSurfaceClick`

## Pre-merge checks (playback-adjacent UI)

```bash
npm run audit:playback-arch
npm run test:playback
```

## Quality bar

The platform should feel **premium**: confident typography, deliberate spacing, smooth micro-interactions, clear hierarchy. Playback behavior must remain unchanged when only visual files differ.
